00:35:36.660 --> 00:35:41.990
just above the valence band.
But the electrons are sitting in

00:35:41.990 --> 00:35:47.330
the valence band,
so how do I get the electrons out of

00:35:47.330 --> 00:35:52.190
the valence band up into this level?
Thermal excitation.

00:35:52.190 --> 00:35:56.590
And guess what this energy
difference is.

00:35:56.590 --> 00:36:00.990
It is on the order of the thermal
energy, and so I get thermal

00:36:00.990 --> 00:36:05.390
ionization of the valence electrons
up into this level.

00:36:05.390 --> 00:36:09.790
This level is a place where
electrons go. It accepts electrons.

00:36:09.790 --> 00:36:23.713
It is called the acceptor level.

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:23.630
So now we have this configuration.
Conduction band, valence band,

00:36:23.630 --> 00:36:29.270
subvalent impurity.
This is not to scale,

00:36:29.270 --> 00:36:34.900
of course. This is on the order of
0.02 eV. And this is called the

00:36:34.900 --> 00:36:40.540
acceptor level.
We get thermal excitation leaving

00:36:40.540 --> 00:36:46.180
holes behind. Thermal excitation
promotes the electrons up to here

00:36:46.180 --> 00:36:51.210
and leaves behind holes.
Every time I put in a subvalent

00:36:51.210 --> 00:36:55.640
impurity the result is a hole,
so I can control the hole population.

00:36:55.640 --> 00:37:00.070
And the same thing will happen,
if you go through this analogy what

00:37:00.070 --> 00:37:04.490
will happen? N will no longer equal
p. Instead, the number of positives

00:37:04.490 --> 00:37:08.920
is going to exceed the number of
negatives. Now ne will be much less

00:37:08.920 --> 00:37:13.350
than nh. N will be less than p.
And so this material will be

00:37:13.350 --> 00:37:17.780
rendered a positive conductor.
It is going to be dominantly hole

00:37:17.780 --> 00:37:24.280
conduction.
So this is now an extrinsic p-type

00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:32.850
semiconductor.
What is the template here?

00:37:32.850 --> 00:37:41.420
Subvalent dopant calls for
electrons, generates holes and makes

00:37:41.420 --> 00:37:55.440
a p-type semiconductor.
That is amazing.

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:55.160
Now I can take these and make a
sandwich out of these things.

00:37:55.160 --> 00:38:00.330
I can do this. This is all silicon.
I could dope this side with

00:38:00.330 --> 00:38:05.490
phosphorus. Let's say the right is
phosphorus doped and the left side

00:38:05.490 --> 00:38:10.660
is boron doped.
That means the left side will be

00:38:10.660 --> 00:38:15.830
p-type, the right side will be
n-type. And what do I have here?

00:38:15.830 --> 00:38:34.193
I have a p-n junction. I have a
solid state rectifier.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:25.300
If I put an AC signal in here,
I get rectification. This is the

00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:29.610
solid state. It is fantastic.
