00:39:31.050 --> 00:39:34.200
The difference in electronegativity.
These are covalent bonds,

00:39:34.200 --> 00:39:37.360
greater difference in
electronegativity,

00:39:37.360 --> 00:39:40.520
higher bond energy.
And that occurs in all of these

00:39:40.520 --> 00:39:43.680
columns as you go up.
So an increase in electronegativity

00:39:43.680 --> 00:39:46.840
difference is an increase in bond
strength, and an increase in bond

00:39:46.840 --> 00:40:06.680
strength means an increase
in band gap energy.

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:34.000
And some of these are really
